"content": "<p>Players of musical instruments. Levitical musicians played an extensive role in Israelite worship. Other musicians are also mentioned in Scripture, in both sacred and secular contexts.</p>\n<h2>Levitical musicians in the tabernacle</h2>\n<h3>Appointed by David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:31-1Chr6:47\">1CH 6:31–6:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:16-1Chr15:17\">1CH 15:16–15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1-1Chr25:5\">1CH 25:1–25:5</a></p>\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:19-1Chr15:21\">1CH 15:19–15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:16\">1CH 15:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:6-1Chr25:7\">1CH 25:6–25:7</a></p>\n<h3>Allocation of duties</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:8-1Chr25:31\">1CH 25:8–25:31</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Levitical musicians in the temple</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:12-2Chr5:13\">2CH 5:12–5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:33\">1CH 9:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:15\">2CH 35:15</a></p>\n<h2>Other musicians</h2>\n<h3>Jubal was the first musician</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:17-Gen4:21\">GEN 4:17–4:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>King David was a renowned musician</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:15-1Sam16:18\">1SA 16:15–16:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:23\">1SA 16:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10-1Sam18:11\">1SA 18:10–18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9-1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:9–19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:5\">2SA 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:1\">2SA 23:1</a></p>\n<h3>Unidentified musicians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:24-Ps68:25\">PSA 68:24–68:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:11-2Kgs3:19\">2KI 3:11–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:1-Ps137:3\">PSA 137:1–137:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:21-Rev18:22\">REV 18:21–18:22</a></p>",
